text.tspan: Air pollution vs. GDP per capita, 1700 to 2016
Levels of air pollution, measured as suspended particulate matter (micrograms per cubic meter) vs. GDP per
capita (2011 international-$). Here, data for London and Delhi GDP levels are assumed to be in line with
national average values for the UK and India.
Data source: Air pollution by city - Fouquet and DPCC (2011); Real GDP per capita, London and Delhi (OWID)
